p: Compounds 14, 15, 19, 20, 24, 37, 41, 42, 48, 51, 52, 54, 55, 57, 64, 69, 70, 71, 72, 74, and 76 were identified as aromatic compounds. The high content of di-tert-butylphenol (compound 54) was found in the ICS leaves, which is reported to have antifungal and antioxidant activities [ 46]. Compound 54 was used as an example to elucidate the identification work of these aromatics. The mass spectrum of compound 54 showed that the molecular ion at m/z 206.2 and the fragment ions were m/z 191.1, 175.1, 163.1, 147.1, 128.1, 107.0, 91.0, 74.0, 66.0, 57.1, 51.0, 40.0, and 32.0, respectively. The mass spectral matching result showed that 2,4-di-tert-butylphenol had a high matching score of 92. The retention index of compound 54 was 1515, which was the similar to the reference retention index 1519. The compound 54 was identified as 2,4-di-tert-butylphenol.
